Implementation details for orders and payments:

Models:

+ Order (Auditable) table = orders
    * id
    * user many-to-one relation with User - user posting the order
    * items one-to-many relation with OrderItem - order items
    * orderDate - order date
    * totalAmount
    * status (pending, in_progress, shipped, delivered, completed, cancelled) - order are placed in pending status
    * shipping address many-to-one relation with Address
    * payment one-to-one relation with Payment

+ OrderItem (Auditable) table = order_items
    * id
    * order many-to-one relation with Order - related order for this item
    * product many-to-one relation with Product - related product for this item
    * quantity (min=1)
    * price
    * discount

+ Payment (Auditable) table = payments
    * id
    * one-to-one relation with order - related order for this payment
    * method (string, minlength=4) - payment method (card, paypal, etc)
    * pgPaymentId: string - payment gateway id
    * pgStatus: string - payment gateway status
    * pgResponse: string - payment gateway response
    * pgName string - payment gateway name

Controllers:
+ OrderController
    * POST 201 /api/orders (request body = OrderCreateRequest, response OrderDetailResponse)
    Sample request
    {
      "addressId": 1,
      "paymentMethod": "card",
      "pgName": "Stripe",
      "pgPaymentId": "pi_1FHEhK2eZvKYlo2CcK4UJNdW",
      "pgStatus": "succeeded",
      "pgResponseMessage": "Payment successful"
    }
    it calls OrderService.placeOrder(...)

Services:
+ OrderService
    * placeOrder(email, addressId, paymentMethod, pgName, pgPaymentId, pgStatus, pgResponse)
    This method will do the following actions:
    1. get user cart and address
    2. create a new order with payment info (define a constructor in Payment entity for: paymentMethod, pgName, pgPaymentId, pgStatus, pgResponse)
    3. get items from cart and create the order items
    4. update product stocks
    5. clear the cart
    6. return the order details

DTOs:
* OrderCreateRequest - used for creating a new order
  + addressId
  + paymentMethod
  + pgName
  + pgPaymentId
  + pgStatus
  + pgResponse
* OrderDetailResponse - order details returned after placing a new order
  + id
  + email - expose only user email
  + items - list of OrderItemDetail DTO
  + orderDate
  + totalAmount
  + status
  + shippingAddress - address Id
  + payment - PaymentDetail DTO

Repositories:
* OrderRepository
* OrderItemRepository
* PaymentRepository

